<Content>Double bookings - dumped at another hotel I was reading the reviews since we are visiting Bali again next year for our wedding and was considering whether to book the Alila Ubud for some relatives to stay. It seems a nice place. My cautious approach comes from the fact that me and my boyfriend booked last year (summer '07) and arrived, only to be told upon arrival that there were double bookings and we could not stay.If only they had the decency to contact us prior to our arrival (they must have known this, because they were preparing for a wedding party - we could see that!), then we would not have bothered travelling from Seminyak to Ubud and extended our stay in Seminyak.They offered us an 'upgrade' to another resort to a private pool villa, and being a bit overthrown, we cared to take a look but the room was hideous, outdated and the resort in the process of being renovated. If they compare themselves that standard they were offering instead, then Allila can't think they are good themselves. We were literally dropped off at this other resort, because the driver from Alila did not wait for us to check that we were ok. We tried to call the Alila various times after deciding we did not want to stay in this other resort, but we never got any phonecall back to help to sort us out, or offering us a taxi ride to where we wanted to go or to ask whether the other resort was satisfactory.Needless to say that, despite the Alila looking beautiful, especially the pool, we did not keep the Alila Ubud on the list as a potential location for our own wedding. 
