<Content>Surprisingly average The Alila Ubud's tag line Surprisingly different... cleverly fails to describe what difference is in store to surprise its guests. Coming from a wonderful two nights at Uma Ubud, Alila's remote location (a 15 minute drive north of Ubud centre) and uninspiring atmosphere felt like an nasty glitch on the travel plan.The grand infinity pool is the only real gem in the resort: the villas are old and tired and the paths and walls are in desperate need of maintenance. One member of staff even confided that working at Alila was difficult [because] the different pay scales for management makes everyone unhappy. Certainly, the service I encountered was well below par.The restaurant is OK although the choices were running out within a day or two. The complimentary afternoon tea is a great service but 30 minutes into the 15:00 - 17:00 slot you will be lucky to find anything left. If you are looking for a remote break and don't mind being a long way from the centre of Ubud, this place may suit your desires. If you wish for more freedom than the four free shuttle buses offer then I would suggest staying somewhere else. In brief, the only surprisingly different thing about the Alila is the price tag in comparison to much nicer places nearer town offering a much better service. 
