<Author>kingfisher
<Content>Luxury Alila UbudStayed here for 2 nights, as our friends were having a wedding here.Ubud, located near the centre of Bali is 1-1.5 hrs drive from the international airport. There is a small town centre nearby with some restaurants, market and monkey forest.Hotel: This is located 10 minutes from the town centre, located near the Ayung river and amongst rainforest and rice fields. Very beautifulRoom: We chose a Superior room. Each building contains 4 rooms. Two deluxe rooms on the ground floor and two superior rooms on the top floor. There is also a small number of villas. The superior room differs to the deluxe room, having no outdoor shower and no garden/patio. The superior was beautiful inside. High thatched ceiling, with a large king sized bed and the white pillows and linen. Extremely smooth comforytabble. A desk is provided. Large cupboard containing an electronic safe. Opening the large glass doors opened up to a balcony with an ottoman, 2 tables and a chair. The room was very tastefully decorated, very clean maintained in excellent condition. Turned down daily and they light a candle and mosquito coil outside on the patio. Air conditioner is strong. Complimentary bottle water is provided in bathroom and main room.Bathroom: modernly decorated, with large shower. The water hot, but pressure poor. Toilietries provided ( unclear what brand), and high quality towels.Pool: has an infinity pool, considered to be in the Top 50 pools in the world. 25m long, and has stunning views of the forest. Lots of deck chairs and complimentary refreshments provided. Clean.Library room: contains two internet terminals- free use, and books, chess, board games.Staff: very friendly, always greeted with smiles at reception to the pool to the restaurant. Apart from lying in the pool, there is a spa ( didnot try), and other activies (cycling). Hotel taxi service available which is the only way to get around from the hotel. A walking/cycling map is provided where you can do you own walking trip around Alila nearby temples and villages, but would recommend to avoid this as there are stray/wild dogs roaming around.Breakfast: We only had breakfast there (included). Excellent - al carte menu (but can order as much as you need). A mix of standard eggs/bacon/toast to indonesians dishes and congee. Also fruits and different types of freshly squeezed juices. Cant comment on the restaurant food during lunch or dinner, but as a surrogate, the restaurant did cook for the wedding reception dinner - a buffest of indonesian food, and there barbeque foods were delicious.Overall: Would recommend this place, if looking for a very romantic getaway or a quiet escape. We paid US$180 per night for two ( including breakfast ). There is not much around, and takes at least an 1hr to get to tourist spots (ie Kuta), so this is a place ideally to unwind and relax. 
