<Content>Overrated We were very excited about our stay - but ended up disappointed. We were in a deluxe room (don't be fooled, these are the basic rooms) which was really small, compared to the fantastic villa we had in Benoa for less then half the price!) It was nicely done, but not Balinese at all, and we felt a little bit stark. We arrived at lunchtime - ordered food and proceeded to wait a LONG time. A couple who ordered food after us were given complimentary drinks because of the wait, but we weren't. Another guest was complaining about another issue at the same time, so it wasn't the best introduction. The setting and pool are gorgous, but as others have said there are nowhere near enough loungers, so people were lying on the floor - not what you expect from a 5 star hotel.The restaurant was pretty terrible - the worst nasi goreng I had in 2 weeks by far. The shuttle isn't regular enough, and the town of Ubud is fantastic - loads of lovely restaurants, and quiet away from the main streets - I would really recommend staying in the town. One absolute positive - the breakfast is fantastic - and free room delivery is well worth it!Overall, I think it just doesn't stack up with other 5 star hotels - the comparison to the Oberoi Seminyak is laughable - now that really is worth it! 
